Not on the dire charm aspect, but it has always been true that if the charmed mob does all the damage then it gets more xp.<br>
<br>
The big change is in the Command of Druzzil class of charms.  This change is being mirrored in the Necro and Druid Charms of similar level.  In the past, these charms had a huge resist adjust (-50).  This was removed in mid-March on the Test Server to a 0 (see Lucy for details).<br>
<br>
So, why are they doing this?  Add in Howl of Tashan and Command of Druzzil with Total Domination and people were getting pretty close to 8 minutes of charming all the time.  Thus as has been yelled about in many forums, enchanters with a lot of skill, luck and intestinal fortitude could solo Tier 3 mini-bosses with charmed pets.<br>
<br>
So, yes Command of Druzzil is returning to the same resist adjust as Beckon.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
